---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Multiple stellar populations in globular clusters";
import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Multiple stellar populations in globular clusters</h1>

    <p><strong>Multiple stellar populations</strong> (MPs) refers to the presence of chemically distinct sub-populations within globular clusters, commonly evidenced by spreads in light elements and helium. MPs are central to understanding cluster formation and early chemical enrichment.</p>

    <h2>Observational diagnostics</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Color--magnitude diagram splits and spreads</li>
      <li>Spectroscopic variations in Na–O, Mg–Al, and helium-sensitive features</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Relevant papers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/lardo_2026_gc_progenitors" text="Lardo et al. (2026)" /> — Hierarchical CMD modelling of MPs in 69 GCs.</li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Base>
